{{Infobox legislature | name = City of Ely Council | legislature = | coa_pic = | coa_res = 100px | coa_caption = Coat of arms | coa_alt = | logo_pic = | logo_caption = Council logo | logo_res = 150px | logo_alt = | foundation = 1 April 1974 | preceded_by = City of Ely Urban District Council | new_session = | house_type = [[Parish councils in England|Parish council]] | jurisdiction = Ely, Cambridgeshire | houses = [[Unicameral]] | term_limits = | leader1_type = | leader1 = | party1 = | election1 = | leader2_type = | leader2 = | party2 = | election2 = | members = | political_groups1 = | house1 = | house2 = | committees1 = | committees2 = | joint_committees = | voting_system1 = | last_election1 = | next_election1 = | session_room = | session_res = 200px | meeting_place = Sessions House, Lynn Road, Ely | motto = | constitution = | website = {{URL|www.cityofelycouncil.org.uk}} | footnotes = }} '''City of Ely Council''' is the [[Parish councils in England|parish council]] responsible for local government within the [[Civil parishes in England|civil parish]] of the city of [[Ely, Cambridgeshire]].
The parish council was formed on 1 April 1974 as a [[successor parish|successor authority]] of the City of Ely Urban District Council. The parish council derives its powers and functions from the Local Government Act 1972 and subsequent legislation.
The civil parish of Ely is divided into four wards called Ely North, Ely South, Ely East and Ely West for the purpose of electing the fourteen councillors to the parish council.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.cityofelycouncil.org.uk/page/1rwtb/Councillors.html | title= Councillors }}</ref>
It is a [[precepting authority]], with tax collected on its behalf by [[East Cambridgeshire District Council]].
