'''Elymnion''' ({{lang-grc|Ἐλύμνιον}}, {{lang-la|Elymnium}}) was an [[Ancient Greece|ancient]] town of [[Euboea]], [[Greece]]. It is mentioned in the play ''[[Peace (play)|Peace]]'' by [[Aristophanes]]. The exact location is unknown, and several possible locations have been suggested, including the present town [[Limni, Euboea|Limni]] on the coast of the [[North Euboean Gulf]]. The modern municipal unit [[Elymnioi]] took its name from ancient Elymnion.

