==Former drivers==
'''[[Louis Chiron]]''' was [[Monaco]]'s first [[Formula One]] driver. He is better known for his pre-war efforts in [[motorsport]], having won 21 Grands Prix (including the [[1931 Monaco Grand Prix]]) before the World Championship began in [[1950 Formula One season|1950]]. He was an elder statesman, as he was 50 when the [[1950 British Grand Prix|first World Championship Grand Prix]] came around. His only points finish was a 3rd at his home race in [[1950 Monaco Grand Prix|Monaco in 1950]]. He did the full [[1951 Formula One season|1951 season]] bar the [[1951 Indianapolis 500|Indy 500]] and only made sporadic appearances after that. He is still the oldest person to enter a Grand Prix, being 58 years and 288 days old when he failed to qualify for his final race, the [[1958 Monaco Grand Prix]].<ref>{{cite news| last =Spurgeon| first =Brad| title =Measuring Experience in Youthful Formula One| newspaper =The New York Times| publisher =The New York Times Company| date =22 August 2009| url =https://www.nytimes.com/2009/08/23/sports/autoracing/23prix.html?_r=0| access-date =21 March 2017}}</ref>

'''[[André Testut]]''' entered in his [[Monaco Grand Prix|home race]] on 2 occasions – 1958 and [[1959 Monaco Grand Prix|1959]]. Both times he failed to qualify his privateer [[Maserati 250F]].

45 years after Testut failed to make the grid in 1959, '''[[Olivier Beretta]]''' was signed by [[Larrousse]] for the [[1994 Formula One season|1994 season]]. He competed in 10 Grands Prix with a best result of 7th at the [[1994 German Grand Prix|German Grand Prix]] before his sponsorship money ran out and was replaced with [[Philippe Alliot]]. He finished 8th in his only attempt at his [[1994 Monaco Grand Prix|home race]]. He later switched his focus to sports-cars.

Dutch-born '''[[Robert Doornbos]]''' competed under a Monegasque license due to FIA license regulation in 2005,<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.fia.com:80/sport/Championships/F1/F1_Season_Guide/2005.html |title=FIA Formula One World Championship Season Guide 2005 |publisher=FIA |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20060408103555/http://www.fia.com/sport/Championships/F1/F1_Season_Guide/2005.html |archivedate=8 April 2006 |accessdate=26 August 2017 |df= }}</ref></small> before representing the [[Netherlands]] in 2006.

