The '''Gabriel Tucker Bridge''' formerly the '''People’s Bridge''', is a [[bridge]] over the [[Mesurado River]] in [[Monrovia]], [[Liberia]]. It was built between 1972 and 1976. The construction caused some minor disruption to local settlements and the [[Liberian National Museum]] had to be relocated in the mid-1970s to facilitate the structure.<ref>[http://www.micat.gov.lr/content.php?sub=National%20Museum&?related=Culture Ministry of Information of the Government of the Republic of Liberia] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170515010101/http://www.micat.gov.lr/content.php?sub=National+Museum&%3Frelated=Culture |date=2017-05-15 }} Retrieved on May 4, 2008</ref> It was designed by [[Gabriel Johnson Tucker]], who Liberian President [[William R. Tolbert]] had named in his honor.<ref>{{cite news |title=Gabriel Johnson Tucker Is Dead |url=http://www.liberianobserver.com/content/gabriel-johnson-tucker-dead-update-0 |accessdate=27 June 2011 |newspaper=Daily Observer |date=April 17, 2011 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110625184244/http://www.liberianobserver.com/content/gabriel-johnson-tucker-dead-update-0 |archivedate=25 June 2011 |df= }}</ref> 

The bridge connects United Nations Drive to [[Bushrod Island]] via [[Providence Island, Monrovia|Providence Island]].<ref>[http://www.tlcafrica.com/tlc_monmaps2.htm www.tlcafrica.com] Retrieved on May 4, 2008</ref>

