{{Infobox organization | name = Nigerian Body of Benchers | image = | size = | alt = <!-- alt text; see [[WP:ALT]] --> | caption = | motto = | lifetime = | extinction = <!-- date of extinction, optional --> | type = Professional Association | status = <!-- ad hoc, treaty, foundation, etc --> | purpose = Regulate legal professionalism | headquarters = | location = | coords = <!-- Coordinates of location using a coordinates template --> | region_served = [[Nigeria]] | membership = Renewable | language = English | leader_title = Chairman | leader_name = [[Chief Bamidele A. Aiku]], OON SAN | general = | website = }}
The '''Nigerian Body of Benchers''' is a professional body concerned with the admission of prospective student into the [[Nigerian Law School]]. Members of the body are called ''[[Benchers]]''. <ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.punchng.com/news/stop-begging-for-failed-law-school-students-benchers-warn/|title=Stop begging for failed law school students, Benchers warn|work=The Punch - Nigeria's Most Widely Read Newspaper|accessdate=24 April 2015|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150106004437/http://www.punchng.com/news/stop-begging-for-failed-law-school-students-benchers-warn/|archivedate=6 January 2015|df=}}</ref> The body also regulate the call of graduate of law school to the Nigerian Bar as well as the regulation of the legal profession in Nigeria.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.punchng.com/news/sofola-emerges-body-of-benchers-chairman/|title=Sofola emerges Body of Benchers’ chairman|work=The Punch - Nigeria's Most Widely Read Newspaper|accessdate=24 April 2015|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120503041014/http://www.punchng.com/news/sofola-emerges-body-of-benchers-chairman/|archivedate=3 May 2012|df=}}</ref>
==Principal officers== The chairman of the body is [[Tribal chief|Chief]] [[T.J.O Okpoko]] who was elected on March 30, 2014 to succeed [[Aloma Mariam Mukhtar]] the [[Chief Justice of Nigeria]] and [[Mahmud Mohammed]] is the vice president.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thisdaylive.com/articles/oyinlola-3-896-others-pass-nigerian-bar-exam/131255/|title=Oyinlola, 3,896 Others Pass Nigerian Bar Exam, Articles - THISDAY LIVE|work=thisdaylive.com|accessdate=24 April 2015|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150725214559/http://www.thisdaylive.com/articles/oyinlola-3-896-others-pass-nigerian-bar-exam/131255/|archivedate=25 July 2015|df=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://allafrica.com/stories/201304161274.html|title=Nigeria: CJN Now Chairman Body of Benchers|work=allAfrica.com|accessdate=24 April 2014}}</ref>
