The '''Tunisian National Guard''' ({{lang-aeb|الحرس الوطني, el-Ḥaras el-Waṭanī}}) is a separate military force of [[Tunisia]]. It is not part of the [[Tunisian Armed Forces]], due to its specific role as a counterbalance to the regular military. It serves both as defence force against external threats and as a security force against internal threats. It is both a standing force of 15,000.
==Vessels and motorboats==
* 6 patrol boats P350TN (140 t, 35 m), donated by Italy (2 delivered 12.2012; 3 delivered between 2013/2014; 1 will be delivery within 2.2015) * 7 patrol boats ''Classe 800/P58'' (30 t, 17 m), donated by [[Italy]] middle years '00 * 4 patrol boats ''Classe 700'' (18 t, 15 m), donated by [[Italy]] in May 2011 * 8 patrol boats ''Classe Squalo'' (13 t, 13,5 m), donated by [[Italy]] middle years '00 * 2 motorboats ''Classe 500'' (8,5 t, 11 m), donated by [[Italy]] in 2009/2011 * 3 Helicopters "Bell 429"
